  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_04_xxv: There is, who without so much as a coat; and there is, who without so much as...",
  "body": "There is, who without so much as a coat; and there is, who without so much as a book, doth put philosophy in practice. I am half naked, neither have I bread to eat, and yet I depart not from reason, saith one. But I say; I want the food of good teaching, and instructions, and yet I depart not from reason.",
